[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Aggregate the ADT Stream to Hourly Counts
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This step consumes raw ADT registration records and bucket them into hourly counts per ED per ESI level. Records arrive in roughly chronological order from the stream, but late-arriving records (the EHR queue lagged for a few minutes) and out-of-order records are normal. In production this is an AWS Glue Streaming job (or EMR Serverless with Spark Structured Streaming) reading from Kinesis with an explicit watermark and a late-record reconciliation pass. The demo does the equivalent in pure Python over the in-memory stream.
