[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     See pseudocode Step 1 in the main recipe. The output is a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     list of rows, one per (ed_id, hour) pair, with per-ESI
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     counts and a total. Records without an ESI level get bucketed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     into `esi_unknown` and reconciled later when triage completes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Two layers: first by (ed_id, local_hour), then by ESI level.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hourly_buckets = defaultdict(lambda: {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "esi_1":        0, "esi_2": 0, "esi_3": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "esi_4":        0, "esi_5": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "esi_unknown":  0,
